                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14014385" author="asuresh" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 23:50:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A log4j properties file can now be specified in the commandLine like so :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ ./bin/sentry --log4jConf &amp;lt;location of properties file&amp;gt; --command service .....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &apos;log4jConf&apos; option and value MUST be the first option after the &apos;sentry&apos; command..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016166" author="sravya" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 03:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like all the command line options which SentryMain does not recognize (the ones SentryService uses, for example) should follow the ones which it does because of stopAtNonOption=false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So even this works: &lt;br/&gt;
bin/sentry --command service --log4jConf /tmp/log4j.properties --conffile /tmp/sentry-site.xml&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016169" author="sravya" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 03:02:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, config file parameter looks like is being used by all three tools invoked from SentryMain, so might as well bring it into SentryMain. But we can do that in a follow on if you prefer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016171" author="sravya" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 03:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 otherwise. Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SENTRY-242&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SENTRY-242&lt;/a&gt; to track order of parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016176" author="sravya" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 03:16:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to the master, thanks Arun!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
